We have an amazing team
of wardrobe staff dressers

00:16:49.090 --> 00:16:50.140
backstage.

00:16:50.140 --> 00:16:51.400
And each piece is handmade.

00:16:51.400 --> 00:16:53.650
They didn't just go somewhere
to go to Barney's Rack

00:16:53.650 --> 00:16:55.000
and buy it or something.

00:16:55.000 --> 00:16:56.382
I mean, each one is designed--

00:16:56.382 --> 00:16:57.840
CHRISTY ALTOMARE:
The rhinestones--

00:16:57.840 --> 00:16:58.180
JOHN BOLTON: Hundreds.

00:16:58.180 --> 00:16:59.388
CHRISTY ALTOMARE: Themselves.

00:16:59.388 --> 00:17:01.990
Like, I remember, the
assistant was saying,

00:17:01.990 --> 00:17:03.580
we've been up for
three days sewing

00:17:03.580 --> 00:17:05.300
in rhinestones on your dress.

00:17:05.300 --> 00:17:06.009
And it really is.

00:17:06.009 --> 00:17:08.424
When you look at it, there's
just rhinestones every-- it's

00:17:08.424 --> 00:17:09.190
beautiful.

00:17:09.190 --> 00:17:12.430
JOHN BOLTON: And the tsarina,
Alexandra, her first dress,

00:17:12.430 --> 00:17:14.440
when she first
comes out, seconds

